title: Gas container explodes in restaurant in east China; 17 dead - International - World
text:
Related 2 dead, 8 trapped after blast in coal mine in eastern China UPDATED: Six killed by multiple China letter bombs: state media China's Xi says to commit 8,000 troops for UN peacekeeping force China chemical plant explosion kills five Authorities in eastern China says 17 people have been killed after a liquefied gas container exploded in a restaurant, causing a fire.
The Wuhu city government's microblog says the explosion happened just before noon Saturday at a small privately run restaurant in the city's Jinghu district.
Wuhu is in Anhui province.
